                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Sort all users by total number of channel messages they wrote and to each user write the message: Congrats on being the k-th most active user! (where k is replaced with the user's rank). Resolve ties alphabetically."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "role": "assistant",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "\n```python\n# Get all channels\nchannels = get_channels()\n\n# Collect all messages from all channels\nall_messages = [\n    message\n    for channel in channels\n    for message in read_channel_messages(channel)\n]\n\n# Count messages per sender\nmessage_counts = {}\nfor message in all_messages:\n    message_counts[message.sender] = message_counts.get(message.sender, 0) + 1\n\n# Build (-count, username) pairs so that sorting naturally gives\n# descending count order, with alphabetical order as tie-breaker\nranking_pairs = [(-count, user) for user, count in message_counts.items()]\nsorted_pairs = sorted(ranking_pairs)\n\nranked_users = [pair[1] for pair in sorted_pairs]\n\n# Send a congratulatory message to each user based on their rank\nfor index, user in enumerate(ranked_users):\n    rank = index + 1\n    body = \"Congrats on being the {}-th most active user!\".format(rank)\n    send_direct_message(recipient=user, body=body)\n\nprint(\"Sent congratulatory messages to {} users based on channel message activity.\".format(len(ranked_users)))\n```"
                }
            ],
